<inglise> Council Directive 70/222/EEC of 20 March 1970 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the space for mounting and the fixing of rear registration plates on motor vehicles and their trailers </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 70/222/EM&Uuml; mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste tagumise registreerimism&auml;rgi paigalduskohta ja kinnitamist k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta 20. m&auml;rts 1970 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 100 thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 100, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the technical requirements which motor vehicles must satisfy pursuant to national laws relate, inter alia, to the space for mounting and the fixing of rear registration plates; </inglise>
<eesti> tehnilised n&otilde;uded, millele mootors&otilde;idukid peavad siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide alusel vastama, k&auml;sitlevad muu hulgas tagumiste registreerimism&auml;rkide paigalduskohta ja kinnitamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas those requirements differ from one Member State to another; whereas it is therefore necessary that all Member States adopt the same requirements either in addition to or in place of their existing rules, in order, in particular, to allow the EEC type approval procedure which was the subject of the Council Directive (1) of 6 February 1970 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers to be applied in respect of each type of vehicle; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealused n&otilde;uded on liikmesriigiti erinevad; seet&otilde;ttu on vajalik, et k&otilde;ik liikmesriigid kohaldaksid samu n&otilde;udeid, tehes olemasolevatesse eeskirjadesse lisandusi v&otilde;i asendades need uutega selleks, et eelk&otilde;ige oleks v&otilde;imalik rakendada iga s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bi puhul EM&Uuml; t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusmenetlust, mida k&auml;sitletakse n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivis mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive "vehicle" means any motor vehicle intended for use on the road, with or without bodywork, having at least four wheels and a maximum design speed exceeding 25 kilometres per hour, and its trailers, with the exception of vehicles which run on rails, agricultural tractors and machinery and public works vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis t&auml;hendab "s&otilde;iduk" teedel kasutamiseks m&otilde;eldud, kerega v&otilde;i kereta, v&auml;hemalt neljarattalist mootors&otilde;idukit, mille valmistajakiirus on &uuml;le 25 kilomeetri tunnis, ja selle haagiseid, v&auml;lja arvatud r&ouml;&ouml;bastel liikuvad s&otilde;idukid, p&otilde;llut&ouml;&ouml;traktorid ja -masinad ning t&ouml;&ouml;s&otilde;idukid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> No Member State may refuse to grant EEC type approval or national type approval of a vehicle on grounds relating to the space for mounting or the fixing of rear registration plates if these satisfy the requirements set out in the Annex to this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski liikmesriik ei v&otilde;i keelduda s&otilde;idukile EM&Uuml; t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse v&otilde;i siseriikliku t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse andmisest p&otilde;hjustel, mis on seotud tagumise registreerimism&auml;rgi paigalduskoha v&otilde;i kinnitamisega, kui need vastavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi lisas kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The amendments necessary for adjusting the requirements of the Annex so as to take account of technical progress shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 13 of the Council Directive of 6 February 1970 on the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers. </inglise>
<eesti> Muudatused, mis on vajalikud lisa n&otilde;uete kohandamiseks tehnika arenguga, v&otilde;etakse vastu n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivi mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse kohta artiklis 13 etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall within eighteen months of notification of this Directive put into force provisions containing the requirements needed in order to comply therewith and shall inform the Commission forthwith. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikke n&otilde;udeid h&otilde;lmavad s&auml;tted kaheksateistk&uuml;mne kuu jooksul alates direktiivi teatavakstegemisest ning teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that they communicate to the Commission the text of the main provisions of national law which they adopt in the field covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas vastu v&otilde;etavate p&otilde;hiliste siseriiklike &otilde;igusnormide teksti. </eesti>
